Introduction

Jung Whee In, better known by her stage name Wheein, is a South Korean singer. She is a member of the girl group MAMAMOO formed by RBW Entertainment. She gained recognition for her appearance on "King of Masked Singer," where she performed as "Half Moon." Before her debut with MAMAMOO, she was a trainee under MBK Entertainment.

Wheein made her solo debut on April 17, 2018, with the digital single "Magnolia." She later parted ways with RBW Entertainment on June 11, 2021.
